PFC 5.0 supports both @func and [func] for calling FISH functions, with different behaviors.

@func() — calls a FISH function and returns its value:
  @setup_triaxial
  @compute_gain(gain_safety)

[func] — evaluates a FISH expression (also calls the function):
  [setup_triaxial]
  [compute_gain(0.5)]

Both work. Use @func for readability at command level.

Important: @func with no parens also calls the function (no-argument call).
  @setup_wall        ; calls setup_wall()
  @track_init         ; calls track_init()
